Phase 2 — Cryptography & Core Vault
All crypto primitives, Zustand store, vault unlock, auth pages
24 tasks  ·  15 security-critical
✓
Task ID
Task Description  (→ indented lines are implementation notes)
☐
P2-001
⚠ Create lib/crypto/utils.ts — toBase64(buffer): string, fromBase64(str): Uint8Array, generateRandomBytes(n): Uint8Array using crypto.getRandomValues
☐
P2-002
⚠ Create lib/crypto/vault.ts — export deriveVaultKey(masterPassword: string, saltBase64: string, iterations = 600_000): Promise<CryptoKey>
  → Use crypto.subtle.importKey with algorithm PBKDF2 and usages ['deriveKey']
  → Use crypto.subtle.deriveKey with {name:'PBKDF2', salt, iterations, hash:'SHA-256'} → {name:'AES-GCM', length:256}
  → Set extractable: false — key must never be extractable from memory as raw bytes
☐
P2-003
⚠ Create lib/crypto/encrypt.ts — export encryptSecret(plaintext: string, key: CryptoKey, aad?: string): Promise<{valueEncrypted: string, iv: string}>
  → Generate fresh 12-byte IV with crypto.getRandomValues every call — never reuse IV
  → Set additionalData to new TextEncoder().encode(aad) when aad is provided
  → tagLength must be 128
  → Return base64-encoded ciphertext and base64-encoded IV
☐
P2-004
⚠ Create lib/crypto/decrypt.ts — export decryptSecret(valueEncrypted: string, iv: string, key: CryptoKey, aad?: string): Promise<string>
  → On AES-GCM auth tag failure, throw a typed error: class DecryptionError extends Error
  → Never log plaintext in catch blocks
  → Return decoded UTF-8 string
☐
P2-005
⚠ Create lib/crypto/share.ts — export encryptShareBundle(secrets: {keyName,plaintext}[], shareKey: CryptoKey): Promise<{bundleEncrypted: string, bundleIv: string}>
  → Serialise the array to JSON, encrypt as a single blob with the share key
  → Return base64 bundleEncrypted + base64 bundleIv
☐
P2-006
⚠ Add decryptShareBundle(bundleEncrypted: string, bundleIv: string, shareKey: CryptoKey) to lib/crypto/share.ts
  → Parse JSON after decryption — return typed array {keyName: string, value: string}[]
☐
P2-007
⚠ Write unit tests for all crypto functions using Node's built-in test runner (node:test)
  → Test round-trip: encrypt then decrypt returns original string
  → Test wrong key → DecryptionError thrown
  → Test wrong AAD → DecryptionError thrown
  → Test IV is never reused across two calls
☐
P2-008
⚠ Create lib/store/vaultStore.ts — Zustand store with fields: derivedKey (CryptoKey|null), isUnlocked (boolean), lastActivity (number, unix ms)
☐
P2-009
Add unlock(key: CryptoKey) action: set derivedKey, isUnlocked=true, lastActivity=Date.now()
☐
P2-010
⚠ Add lock() action: set derivedKey=null, isUnlocked=false
  → This is the ONLY place the key reference is cleared — ensure no other component holds a copy
☐
P2-011
Add touchActivity() action: set lastActivity=Date.now()
☐
P2-012
⚠ Create useAutoLock(timeoutMs) hook in lib/store/vaultStore.ts — setInterval every 30s checks Date.now()-lastActivity > timeoutMs, calls lock() if true. Clears interval on unmount.
☐
P2-013
⚠ Add window.addEventListener('visibilitychange') in the vault layout to call lock() when document becomes hidden (tab switch / phone lock)
☐
P2-014
⚠ Create app/api/vault/salt/route.ts — GET handler. Authenticate session. If user.vaultSalt is null, generate 32 random bytes via crypto.randomBytes (server-side Node), save to DB as base64, return it. Otherwise return existing salt.
  → This is the only salt-generation endpoint — call it once on first vault setup
